Quantitative Data Analyst		Flatiron Health		New York City, NY, US		<div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Our mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud&amp;trade; platform includes the industry-leading electronic medical record for oncology, a first-of-its-kind analytics tool, patient portal, and integrated billing management. Our goal is to help cancer centers and life science companies leverage real-world oncology data at a scale and clinical depth never before seen, to advance cancer care and accelerate research. We&rsquo;ve built a unified data set that is unparalleled in its depth and accuracy and gives our partners the capability to ask questions about data that weren't answerable until now. Our Quantitative Sciences team answers these questions.<br /><br />Our Quantitative Sciences team is looking for team members who are excited to make an immediate impact in a critical space. This position requires outstanding problem-solving, analytical and communication skills, experience with multitasking and prioritizing in a fast-paced environment, and the tenacity to execute against deliverables in a timely, high-quality fashion. The opportunities are endless, but for starters you will work across several active Data &amp; Analytics products, from contractual commitment through successful deployment. You will draw insights from our data and then visualize those insights so that they are useful by varied client audiences. You will develop creative ways to explore and leverage the clinical data in our systems. You will collaborate with a team of salespeople, oncologists, product managers, and software engineers to help develop, commercialize, and deliver our analytics products. Working in a fast-paced and rapidly expanding business, you will be consistently challenged to partner with Flatiron colleagues to create a rock-solid, scalable foundation for explosive growth.<br /> <strong>As a Quantitative Data Analyst you will:</strong> <ul> <li>Become the subject matter expert on our data and its capabilities</li> <li>Transform real-world clinical data into actionable insights using robust statistical methods and compelling data visualizations in formats accessible to a wide range of end users</li> <li>Develop analysis plans, document analytic methods, establish standard operating procedures, and create publication-ready methods and results</li> <li>Work with a cross-functional teams to understand and clarify analytic requirements and identify areas for automation and process efficiencies</li> <li>Generate ideas for analyses to shape future projects, contributing to a pipeline of opportunities that will help Flatiron achieve its ambitious growth goals</li> </ul> <strong>About you:</strong> <ul> <li>You hold a Bachelor&rsquo;s degree in a quantitative discipline, such as biostatistics, epidemiology, applied statistics, applied mathematics, or health economics</li> <li>You have 1-3 years of relevant work experience analyzing real-world clinical data</li> <li>You love working with data and have experience exploring data with a critical and thoughtful eye</li> <li>You excel at R or SAS and have experience working with SQL and/or Tableau</li> <li>You are a brilliant communicator, both oral and written</li> <li>You are self-motivated, thrive in highly uncertain situations, and enjoy coming up with elegant and innovative solutions to challenging problems</li> <li>You are a “do-er”-- you know how to balance attention to detail with quick execution against tight timelines</li> <li>You are flexible and adapt well to complex challenges</li> <li>You are passionate about our mission to improve healthcare through technology</li> <li>You are a highly-effective collaborator and are motivated by the opportunity to work with oncologists, software engineers, product managers, and other members of the Flatiron team</li> </ul> <strong>Bonus points if you:</strong> <ul> <li>Have specific domain knowledge in clinical oncology</li> <li>Have experience working with national epidemiological data sources for oncology (e.g., SEER, NPCR, etc.)</li> <li>Come from a tech company or have experience working with technical teams</li> <li>Have experience visualizing longitudinal patient-level data</li></ul></div><div class="rich-text" itemprop="description">Flatiron Health’s mission is to serve cancer patients and our customers by dramatically improving treatment and accelerating research. Our team is building a disruptive, oncology-specific software platform that connects cancer centers across the world on a common technology infrastructure to address key healthcare challenges. <br /><br />Today, the Flatiron Health OncologyCloud™ platform includes the industry-leading electronic medical record for oncology, a first-of-its-kind analytics tool, patient portal, and integrated billing management. Our goal is to help cancer centers and life science companies leverage real-world oncology data at a scale and clinical depth never before seen to advance cancer care and accelerate research. <br /><br />We are hiring for a number of open positions. Please visit our website for more details.</div>